=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Chain Reverse Field Override) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  MOVE02 -> calc stage 0
C  REVR01 -> calc stage 1 overrides with reversed field 01
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: calc slot 1 can now use REVR01 or REVR02, reusing the raw-field
  reverse helpers and, in the two-output subset, also taking over matching
  output-definition selection from calc slot 0.
- This variant starts with MOVE02, then REVR01 overrides both the calc result
  and the selected detail shape, so the reversed 10-byte field 01 is emitted.

Current runtime-produced output:
A10 DROCER
B20 DROCER
C30 DROCER

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_chain_move2_revr1.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
